%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMassive%20government%20spending%20on%20defense%20is%20costing%20other%20sectors%2C%20Alexandra%20Prokopenko%20wrote.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBusinesses%20are%20slumping%20amid%20inflation%2C%20low%20labor%20supply%2C%20and%20rising%20borrowing%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20numbers%2C%20neither%20Western%20sanctions%20nor%20the%20costs%20of%20three%20years%20of%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20chipped%20at%20Russia's%20growth%20momentum.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20GDP%20is%20expected%20to%20expand%20by%204%25%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYet%20this%20image%20of%20resilience%20is%20deceptive%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexandra%20Prokopenko%20wrote%20for%20Carnegie%20Politika%20this%20week.%20%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20Russia's%20economy%20has%20operated%20like%20a%20marathoner%20on%20fiscal%20steroids%E2%80%94and%20now%20those%20steroids%20are%20wearing%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20this%20won't%20end%20in%20a%20sudden%20collapse%2C%20Russia's%20fixation%20and%20dependence%20on%20wartime%20growth%20has%20created%20the%20irreversible%20threat%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bstagnation%20trap%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Carnegie%20Russia%20Eurasia%20Center%20fellow%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2Frussia-eurasia%2Fpolitika%2F2024%2F12%2Frussia-economy-difficulties%3Flang%3Den%26center%3Drussia-eurasia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20on%20Friday%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProkopenko%20estimates%20that%20economic%20momentum%20will%20stutter%20next%20year%2C%20giving%20way%20to%20social%20and%20fiscal%20upheaval%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff43b6df-e781-4305-9c09-d060cedbcfc9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECracks%20emerge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEconomic%20cracks%20will%20likely%20stem%20from%20the%20same%20thing%20that%20has%20kept%20Russia%20afloat%20since%20it%20first%20invaded%20Ukraine%20in%202022%3A%20the%20Kremlin's%20sweeping%20support%20for%20its%20defense%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20huge%20spending%20in%20the%20sector%20is%20only%20set%20to%20grow%2C%20and%20in%202025%2C%20defense%20and%20security%20spending%20will%20account%20for%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-outlook-defense-budget-spending-ukraine-war-putin-sanctions-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E8%25%20of%20GDP%20and%2040%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20all%20government%20expenditures%2C%20Prokopenko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20comes%20at%20a%20cost%20to%20the%20broader%20economy.%20Budgetary%20allocations%20to%20non-defense%20sectors%20are%20shrinking%2C%20while%20increased%20tax%20revenue%20is%20directed%20almost%20exclusively%20toward%20military%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustries%20that%20don't%20contribute%20to%20defense%20production%20are%20wavering%2C%20such%20as%20commodity%20and%20agriculture%20producers.%20As%20global%20coal%20prices%20slide%2C%20Russia's%20coal%20sector%20is%20suffering%20proper%20losses%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20four%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20big%20deal%2C%20Prokopenko%20said%E2%80%94with%20thirty-one%20single-industry%20towns%20involved%20in%20the%20sector%2C%20a%20single%20shutdown%20can%20debilitate%20a%20whole%20community%2C%20forcing%20the%20government%20to%20step%20in%20with%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20other%20struggling%20industries%E2%80%94automotive%20manufacturing%2C%20non-food%20retail%2C%20and%20housing%20construction%E2%80%94are%20also%20lining%20up%20for%20state%20assistance.%20Resources%20are%20stretched%20thin%20as%20stagnant%20oil%20and%20gas%20revenues%2C%20coupled%20with%20energy%20sanctions%2C%20limit%20budgetary%20inflows.%20While%20tax%20revenues%20have%20temporarily%20offset%20falling%20hydrocarbon%20income%2C%20they%20are%20consumed%20by%20current%20expenditures%2C%20leaving%20no%20surplus%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20long%20central%20authorities%20can%20len